## MASTER IMPLEMENTATION PROMPT

Use this as the top-level instruction when building from these specs:

> Build a simple, light-mode marketing website for Kamiyon Studio using Next.js 16, React 19, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS 4. Implement exactly 7 pages: Home (hero, clients, services, awards, CTA), Portfolio (3-level: hub → category → project for design/illustration/games/branding/3d-motion/web), News (external links only), About, Press kit, and Contact (Google Form embed + mailto + socials, no Calendly). Apply Kamiyon brand: white backgrounds, sakura pink `#f97695` accents, Poppins/Montserrat typography, official logo, subtle Kami-chan. Portfolio uses Fully Illustrated layout patterns in light mode. UI reference: Sakura internet cleanliness. Content from `docs/` and `context/` canon only — labeled placeholders elsewhere. No separate Services, Team, Awards, or Testimonials pages. No dark mode, no on-site blog, no fabricated clients or awards.

